body:
## Problem

`TokenStore.Save()` uses `os.WriteFile` which truncates and writes in place. This creates a race condition:
- If MCP server refreshes token while CLI is reading `auth.json`
- Reader may encounter partial/empty file causing auth failures

## Related PR

Raised in code review for #268

## Proposed Solution

Use atomic write pattern:
1. Write to temporary file in same directory
2. Use `os.Rename()` to atomically replace target file

```go
func (t *TokenStore) Save(auth *StoredAuth) error {
    data, err := json.MarshalIndent(auth, "", "  ")
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }

    // Write to temp file first
    tmpPath := t.path + ".tmp"
    if err := os.WriteFile(tmpPath, data, 0600); err != nil {
        return err
    }

    // Atomic rename
    return os.Rename(tmpPath, t.path)
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Token writes are atomic (no partial reads possible)
- [ ] Temp file cleaned up on error
- [ ] Works on all supported platforms
